## 3. AI image generation

Pick a provider and put the key **only** on a backend/serverless function:

```js
// /api/generate-image  (server-side â€” never expose this key in frontend JS)
const resp = await fetch('https://api.openai.com/v1/images/generations', {
  method: 'POST',
  headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${process.env.OPENAI_API_KEY}`, 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
  body: JSON.stringify({ model: 'dall-e-3', prompt, size: '1024x1024' })
})
```

Then in `aegis-pro.html`, replace the `imgBtn` click handler's placeholder with a `fetch('/api/generate-image', {...})` call to your own backend, and render the returned image URL.

