## 4. Why this couldn't just be "done" in the artifact

A single HTML file in a chat artifact runs entirely client-side with no server, no npm packages, and no ability to hold secrets â€” any API key placed in its JavaScript would be visible to anyone who opens dev tools. Auth, databases with RLS, OAuth, and paid generation APIs all fundamentally require a secret-holding backend. The honest path is: prototype the UX in the artifact (done), then move to a real framework (Next.js + Supabase + a serverless API layer) for production, using this guide as the wiring diagram.

